column1: Arch: Server Naming Convention
column35: Decision needs to be made around server naming convention.  Server names are character limited and proposed site codes are too long.  This decision needs to consider what information is baked into the server name, and what information should be accessible from a CMDB.  Dynamic information, such as location, baked into a server name can lead to, operations and application rework when the asset changed, such as being moved to a different data center.
column245: 16/Sep/21 4:18 PM;kevin.j.kaiser@raytheon.com;A new server naming convention was reviewed and approved in June.  New naming convention is attached.;;;

column1: NET-007-Epic: Managed Service Provider Transition / Migration Plan
column35:
*RADIUS and TACACS access to LAN/WLAN devices owned and/or leased by RTX*
 * Cisco ISE is the go-forward access management tool for RTX

*Historical LAN/WLAN Configurations and heterogenous (cross-vendor) Configuration Deployment:*
 * *This is a gap. There is yet no identified tool that stores or manages configurations across Network equipment providers.*

Determine which ownership model applies to tools and assets, determine the decision milestones and dates, then prioritize the core infrastructure management tools required for break/fix, change management, and incident management for RTX owned Network WAN and DC LAN assets. Apply the suitable tools rationalization decision logic based on these key inputs and communicate to design teams + finance / procurement / partner management on go-forward proposals.
column149:
Acceptance Criteria: Our current MSP has maintained an instance of it so the transition point is the transfer of that data into a RTX Cisco ISE policy node.

Acceptance Criteria: RTX may need to deploy an existing tool to sustain operations in support of MSP transition. This tool has requisite licensing.

column1: NET-007-Standardize and bring up to "X" compliance level for RTX
column35:
*Secrets Management and backdoor access to Network LAN/WLAN devices + network tool communication via SNMPv2/v3*
 * Tools use SNMPv2 and v3 (which requires a username and password) and a SNMP home string to communicate out to devices.
 * SNMPv2 is being used today and the username/password secrets should ideally be rotated by the MSP via a management tool.
 * SNMPv2 is not encrypted, but that depends on the tool reaching out to the devices as well as the target device.

*Disaster Recovery Plan and Business Continuity Policies related to backup Network Device Inventory for LAN/WLAN*
 * In some cases, the MSP reserves devices (ordered by RTX) to be swapped in / utilized in case of device failure.
column149:
Secrets Management and backdoor access to Network LAN/WLAN devices + network tool communication via SNMPv2/v3:
Acceptance Criteria: Successful transition criteria for this epic is the MSP transfer of the secrets (username and password), SNMP home string, and device list showing support for SNMPv2 and/or SNMPv3. If LAN/WLAN/Voice/DDI network devices can be accessed otherwise, this also needs to be documented.

Disaster Recovery Plan and Business Continuity Policies related to backup Network Device Inventory for LAN/WLAN:
Acceptance Criteria 1: An inventory of all backup devices and their locations to transition and sustain support using existing RTX investment.

Acceptance Criteria 2: A certified Disaster Recovery process by RTX as part of BCP that demonstrates what would occur during a DR failover.

Acceptance Criteria 3: A successful DR test or previous tests run by the MSP to demonstrate the documented process to support RTX knowledge

column1: NET-013: Cyber Identity - Infrastructure Dependency: Firewall availability
column35:
Firewall availability/complexity to implement model and required rules for ADX to function properly.

Impact: Clients unable to consume identity services if not able to connect.

Resolution/Mitigation: Need Firewall team resources to implement required rules.

Fortinet Firewall being used b/c need to fix IP conflicts utilizing nating as a TEMPORARY FIX (est 9mo-1yr).  Need a firewall in place so leveraging something already owned before long-term solution is in place.  Long term solution utilizing Nextgen Firewall solution which works with EXSI design.

Need this in and IP Conflicts also resolved so ADX (IDM) can complete work by end of year.

column1: Cyber - Infrastructure dependency: Enterprise DNS resolution
column35:
DNS resolution across the enterprise. All clients that leverage ADX require full DNS resolution regardless of location.

Impact: Clients unable to authenticate to ADX. Clients unable to use kerberos for authentication if DNS registration is not supported. Cannot comply with NIST 800-171 (replay resistant protocols).

Resolution/Mitigation: Need to callout DNS team for resolution across the enterprise. Need dynamic updates to register DNS address in the correct domain for all ADX domain join systems.

Infrastructure: Network, DNS

column1: VAR - If spend data is not accurate, then baseline for synergy targets will not be realized
column35: Spend data is being captured from different procurement systems and is not fully populated in Supplier Insight. Data provided by suppliers may not include everything need to define synergy targets. If we can not accurately define our synergy as a result of poor data, then it will be difficult to prove the achievement of savings.
column245: 06/Jul/21 2:19 PM;Amanda.J.Diduca@raytheon.com;Cancelled: VAR Rationalization effort transitioning to be lead by Enterprise Software (Strategy & Transformation) team (Paula Ardel).;;;

column1: Short timeline for delivery
column35:
* Initial scope = 8 weeks 
 * SOW execution and Cybersecurity approvals delayed kickoff by 1-2 weeks
 * Internal RTX stakeholder requirements pulled date from 6/30 to 6/15
column245: 01/Jun/21 10:29 AM;kevin.barry@rtx.com;Inherent project risk;;;

column1: VAR - If awarded supplier does not have a record in all hUTC systems, then time may be required to follow heritage compliance to onboard the supplier at each business unit
column35: Team will define what systems suppliers are active in while strategic engagement is in process. New suppliers that need to be entered into hRTN system (ESDM), will only take a matter of weeks to onboard the supplier. The current understanding of the hUTC process, is that onboarding can take more than a month for some of the heritage business procurement processes and systems to be updated with new suppleirs.
column245: 06/Jul/21 2:19 PM;Amanda.J.Diduca@raytheon.com;Cancelled: VAR Rationalization effort transitioning to be lead by Enterprise Software (Strategy & Transformation) team (Paula Ardel).;;;

column1: VAR - If non-PSL POs continue to be place for SW purchases, then savings will not be realized
column35: Change management will be critical to the success of realizing the savings. Assuming rate reductions can be achieved, synergy savings will only be met if businesses (through buyers) are able to shift their SW procurement to the new VAR PSL. The team will be working on creating a detailed change management plan to ensure the buying community is educated on the new PSL, including work instructions and updates to procurement systems.
column245: 06/Jul/21 2:20 PM;Amanda.J.Diduca@raytheon.com;Cancelled: VAR Rationalization effort transitioning to be lead by Enterprise Software (Strategy & Transformation) team (Paula Ardel).;;;

column1: VAR - If suppliers are unable or unwilling to amend the existing agreements or provide a Letter of Understanding, then a full CWA process will be followed, extending the timeline
column35: Current approach for achieving synergy targets is by asking suppliers to provide reduced rates for SW purchases. This reduction of rate will be documented through a "Letter of Understanding," which has been successfully used through past, similar efforts. There is a risk that suppliers will not want to sign a letter, and will only reduce rates if we sign a full agreement. If this happens, then we will not be able to achieve savings.
column245: 06/Jul/21 2:20 PM;Amanda.J.Diduca@raytheon.com;Cancelled: VAR Rationalization effort transitioning to be lead by Enterprise Software (Strategy & Transformation) team (Paula Ardel).;;;
